Reasoning: The paper discusses the evaluation and measurement of explainable AI systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also focuses on the user's understanding and satisfaction with the AI system, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper discusses methods for evaluating the goodness of explanations and the user's trust and reliance on the AI, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the human-XAI work system, which relates to information retrieval (cs.IR).
